SIMPLE: honesty
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Honesty
<hw>Hon"es*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>honeste</ets>, <ets>oneste</ets>, honor, OF.
<ets>honest⟦eacute⟧</ets>, <ets>onest⟦eacute⟧</ets> (cf. F.
<ets>honn⟦ecir⟧tet⟦eacute⟧</ets>), L. <ets>honestas</ets>. See
<er>Honest</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Honor;
honorableness; dignity; propriety; suitableness; decency.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She derives her <qex>honesty</qex> and achieves her goodness.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The quality or state of being honest; probity;
fairness and straightforwardness of conduct, speech, etc.; integrity;
sincerity; truthfulness; freedom from fraud or guile.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That we may lead a quiet and peaceable life in all godliness and
<qex>honesty</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>1 Tim. ii. 2.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Chastity; modesty.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To lay . . . siege to the <qex>honesty</qex> of this Ford's
wife.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Satin flower; the name of two
cruciferous herbs having large flat pods, the round shining partitions
of which are more beautiful than the blossom; -- called also
<altname>lunary</altname> and <altname>moonwort</altname>. <spn>Lunaria
biennis</spn> is common honesty; <spn>Lunaria rediva</spn> is perennial
honesty.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Integrity; probity; uprightness; trustiness;
faithfulness; honor; justice; equity; fairness; candor; plain-dealing;
veracity; sincerity.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Honewort</ent>⟦br⟧
